<paragraph id="663E369ADD175A3EFF7AFD89CD92CC0A" blockId="21.[227,436,550,576]" box="[227,436,550,576]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD175A3EFF7AFD89CD92CC0A" bold="true" box="[227,436,550,576]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFF7AFD89CD92CC0A" bold="true" box="[227,436,550,576]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Shell description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD175A3EFF7AFDFACE1FCCB6" blockId="21.[225,1436,597,764]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Moderately large shell (
<quantity id="A1799B7FDD175A3EFE6EFDFACE52CC3A" box="[503,628,597,624]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.114" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="31.14">31.14 mm</quantity>
). Early spire whorls coeloconoid, straight. Middle to late spire whorls convex, elevated, creating conical, bulbous outline. Subsutural flexure deep, strongly curved, strongly asymmetrical (
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD175A3EFE16FD34CDD0CCFC" box="[399,502,667,694]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="61.[227,270,1647,1673]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,912,1604]" captionTargetId="figure-374@61.[227,1437,912,1604]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Fig. 40. Examples of subsutural flexures. A. Conus (Lautoconus) eschewegi Pereira da Costa, 1866 (MNHN.F.A82976). B. Conus (Lautoconus) ictini sp. nov. (AMPG(IV) 3719). C. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 1 (MNHN.F.A82982). D. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 2 (AMPG(IV) 3756). E. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 3 (MNHN.F.A83012). F. Conus (Lautoconus) cf. baldichieri Borson, 1820 (MNHN.F.A83013). G. Conus (Lautoconus) lauriatragei sp. nov. (MNHN.F.A83014). H. Conus (Lautoconus) damianakisi sp. nov. (AMPG(IV) 3802). I. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 4 (MNHN.F.A83015). J. Conus (Lautoconus) sp. 5 (AMPG(IV) 3861). K. Conus (Stephanoconus) cf. taurinensis Bellardi &amp; Michelotti, 1841 (AMPG(IV) 3808). L. Conus (Stephanoconus) moissettei sp. nov. (MNHN.F.A83071). M. Conus davolii sp. nov. (MNHN.F.A83091). N. Conus fuscocingulatus Hörnes, 1851 (AMPG(IV) 3858). O. Conus (Plagioconus) elatus Michelotti, 1847 (AMPG(IV) 3862). P. Conus (Plagioconus) sp. (AMPG(IV) 3890). Q. Conus (Plagioconus) sp. (AMPG(IV) 3898). R. Conus (Plagioconus) aquensis d’Orbigny, 1852 (AMPG(IV) 3907). Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484351/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 40F</figureCitation>
). Shoulder slightly angulated. Maximum diameter right below shoulder.Aperture narrow, widening towards siphonal canal. Last whorl straight to slightly inflated. Siphonal canal short, wide. Fasciole short, twisted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2E9B6511DD175A3EFF7AFC8CCE6BCA28" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="663E369ADD175A3EFF7AFC8CCE69CD77" blockId="21.[227,591,803,829]" box="[227,591,803,829]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD175A3EFF7AFC8CCE69CD77" bold="true" box="[227,591,803,829]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFF7AFC8CCE69CD77" bold="true" box="[227,591,803,829]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description of colour pattern</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD175A3EFF7AFCFDCE6BCA28" blockId="21.[227,1438,850,1122]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The colour pattern consists of three levels of colouration. The first one consists of continuous grouped spiral lines of dim-fluorescent colour (
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD175A3EFD59FCDACF3ACDC5" box="[704,796,885,911]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[227,270,1968,1994]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,724,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-50@22.[227,1437,724,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 12. Elements constituting the colour pattern of Conus (Lautoconus) cf. baldichieri Borson, 1820 from the Tortonian of Crete (Greece), specimen MNHN.F.A83013, shown under UV light. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484291/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
, dim fluorescent lines). The second one consists of continuous spiral lines of bright-fluorescent colour (
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD175A3EFCDFFC37CFB8CDF8" box="[838,926,920,946]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[227,270,1968,1994]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,724,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-50@22.[227,1437,724,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 12. Elements constituting the colour pattern of Conus (Lautoconus) cf. baldichieri Borson, 1820 from the Tortonian of Crete (Greece), specimen MNHN.F.A83013, shown under UV light. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484291/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
, bright green coloured lines). Both patterns of lines are slightly wavy, and it is possible for the second one to overprint the first. The third level of colouration is a series of thin, wavy, fluorescent and axial lines (
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD175A3EFB91FC70C846CDB3" box="[1032,1120,991,1017]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[227,270,1968,1994]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,724,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-50@22.[227,1437,724,1934]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 12. Elements constituting the colour pattern of Conus (Lautoconus) cf. baldichieri Borson, 1820 from the Tortonian of Crete (Greece), specimen MNHN.F.A83013, shown under UV light. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484291/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
, axial lines). The lines are not always continuous, but are more prominent on the spire whorls. Some of the lines are linked one to another, turning into a pattern of axially entangled lines. The result of the three patterns reminds of vehicle tire tracks (
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD175A3EFE5CFBE7CE16CA28" box="[453,560,1096,1122]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,1437,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-361@21.[227,1437,1437,1923]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Conus (Lautoconus) cf. baldichieri Borson, 1820 from the Tortonian of Crete (Greece) on apertural, abapertural and apical views, under natural (A1–A2, A5) and UV light. Specimen MNHN.F.A83013. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484289/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="FEBA2A1FDD175A3EFDA9FBE7CE66CA28" box="[560,576,1096,1122]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[227,270,1858,1884]" captionTargetBox="[227,1437,706,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-133@7.[227,1437,706,1816]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. Conus (Lautoconus) eschewegi Pereira da Costa, 1866 from the Tortonian of Crete (Greece) on apertural and abapertural views, under UV light, displaying morphological and colour pattern variations. A. Specimen MNHN.F.A82973, Crete. B. Specimen MNHN.F.A82974, Crete. C. Specimen AMPG(IV) 3702, Filippi. D. Specimen MNHN.F.A82980, Crete. E. Specimen MNHN.F.A82981. F. Specimen MNHN.FA82978, Crete. G. Specimen AMPG(IV) 3711, Tefeli. H. Specimen AMPG(IV) 3706, Filippi. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484265" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484265/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2E9B6511DD175A3CFF7AFB25CF52CF97" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="663E369ADD175A3EFF7AFB25CD73CAEE" blockId="21.[227,341,1162,1188]" box="[227,341,1162,1188]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD175A3EFF7AFB25CD73CAEE" bold="true" box="[227,341,1162,1188]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFF7AFB25CD73CAEE" bold="true" box="[227,341,1162,1188]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD175A3EFF7AFB16C9BACB15" blockId="21.[226,1437,1208,1376]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD175A3EFF7AFB16CE16CA98" author="Ferrero Mortara E. &amp; Montefameglio L. &amp; Novelli M. &amp; Opesso G. &amp; Pavia G. &amp; Tampieri R." box="[227,560,1208,1235]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 484" refId="ref29411" refString="Ferrero Mortara E., Montefameglio L., Novelli M., Opesso G., Pavia G. &amp; Tampieri R. 1984. Catalogo dei tipi e degli esemplari figurati della collezione Bellardi e Sacco II. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Catalogo 7: 1 - 484." type="journal article" year="1984">
Ferrero Mortara 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFE3FFB16CDFFCA98" box="[422,473,1208,1234]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al</emphasis>
. (1984
</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 16 fig. 8) figured the ‘holotype’ of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD175A3EFC6FFB16C8E7CA98" box="[1014,1217,1208,1235]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="baldchieri">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFC6FFB16C8E7CA98" box="[1014,1217,1208,1235]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Conus baldchieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in fact they made a fixation of a 
<typeStatus id="B93A8838DD175A3EFE0AFB74CDD9CABF" box="[403,511,1243,1269]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">lectotype</typeStatus>
by inference of 
<typeStatus id="B93A8838DD175A3EFD5FFB74CF16CABF" box="[710,816,1243,1269]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
, ICZN 1999: Art. 74.6)) regarded by 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD175A3EFB6BFB73C9BBCABC" author="Sacco F." box="[1266,1437,1244,1270]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref31718" refString="Sacco F. 1893 a. I molluschi dei terreni terziarii del Piemonte e della Liguria. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, Torino." type="book" year="1893">Sacco (1893a)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD175A3EFE9EFB50CE9BCB53" box="[263,701,1279,1305]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Lithoconus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="mercatii" variety="baldichieri">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFE9EFB50CDD1CB52" box="[263,503,1279,1305]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Lithoconus mercatii</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFDA5FB50CE9BCB53" box="[572,701,1279,1305]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">baldichieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The Cretan specimen attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD175A3EFBE7FB50CD42CB76" authorityName="Borson" authorityYear="1820" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="baldichieri" subGenus="Lautoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFBE7FB50C8EFCB53" box="[1150,1225,1279,1305]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFB46FB50C94ECB52" box="[1247,1384,1279,1304]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Lautoconus</emphasis>
) cf. 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFF7AFA8DCD42CB76" box="[227,356,1314,1340]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">baldichieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD175A3EFE61FA8DCF49CB76" authority="Borson, 1820" authorityName="Borson" authorityYear="1820" box="[504,879,1314,1340]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="baldichieri">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD175A3EFE61FA8DCEECCB76" box="[504,714,1314,1340]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Conus baldichieri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD175A3EFD48FA8DCF49CB76" author="Borson S." box="[721,879,1314,1340]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="180 - 229" refId="ref28722" refString="Borson S. 1820. Saggio di Orittografia Piemontese. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino: 180 - 229." type="book chapter" year="1820">Borson, 1820</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Pliocene of 
<collectingCountry id="1E96760ADD175A3EFBF0FA8DC886CB76" box="[1129,1184,1314,1340]" name="Italy" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Italy</collectingCountry>
, but differs in the less striated spire whorls, the less inflated shell, the more elongate last whorl and its shorter siphonal canal.
</paragraph>
<caption id="32FE6612DD175A3EFF7AF802CEB5C644" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484289" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6484289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6484289/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" startId="21.[227,270,1965,1991]" targetBox="[227,1437,1437,1923]" targetPageId="21">
